                Ali founded AgentList in early 2024. Before this, she spent six
                years in the Army as an Aircraft Commander, flying MQ-1C Grey
                Eagles. She logged nearly 1,500 flight hours and was awarded a
                Purple Heart after a missile attack during her deployment to
                Iraq.
            </p>
            <p class="cs-text">
                When Ali decided to leave the Army to raise her family, she
                realized how difficult it was to find a real estate agent who
                understood the specific needs of a service member. She started
                building AgentList while pregnant with her first child to solve
                that problem. Today, as a mom of two, she runs the business with
                one goal: making sure soldiers are taken care of by agents who
                actually fit their needs.
